00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,333
THERE ARE ANY NUMBER OF PLACES
HE MIGHT BE HEADED.

231
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:39,066
- ( gasps )
MILLENNION HEADQUARTERS?

232
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:40,933
- WE'LL BE LEAVING
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

233
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,100
NOW GO GET READY.
WE'VE GOT TO HURRY.

234
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:46,033
- ( gunshots )

235
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,666
( gunshots )

236
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:25,800
- ( clapping )

237
00:13:25,866 --> 00:13:27,400
- ( gun cocks )

238
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:35,000
- IT'S NO MISTAKE.
- YEAH.

239
00:13:35,066 --> 00:13:36,700
HE'S BRANDON HEAT,
ALL RIGHT.

240
00:13:36,766 --> 00:13:39,633
- LONG TIME NO SEE, BRANDON.

241
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:41,400
LOOKS LIKE
THE TIME BOB SPENT

242
00:13:41,466 --> 00:13:44,566
MANIPULATING THAT INFORMATION
WAS A WORTHWHILE INVESTMENT.

243
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:46,233
YOU'RE HERE AFTER ALL.

244
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:48,666
I WONDER IF THAT'S BECAUSE
OF YOUR KEEN SENSE OF DUTY

245
00:13:48,733 --> 00:13:50,433
OR JUST PLAIN STUPIDITY.

246
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,800
EITHER WAY,

247
00:13:51,866 --> 00:13:53,600
YOU'VE DONE PRECISELY
WHAT I THOUGHT YOU'D DO,

248
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:56,500
USE NECROLIZATION TO
COME BACK FROM THE DEAD.

249
00:13:58,466 --> 00:14:00,366
- Bear: BRANDON.

250
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:02,800
HAVE YOU COME
TO TAKE YOUR REVENGE?

251
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,633
BRANDON?

252
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:08,766
- HMM?

253
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,300
- SOMETHING'S
WRONG WITH HIM.

254
00:14:10,366 --> 00:14:13,000
- LOOKS LIKE HE'S HAVING SOME
 KIND OF FUNCTIONAL DISORDER.

255
00:14:13,066 --> 00:14:14,333
- HOW PATHETIC.

256
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,233
- Bob: HOLD ON, BUNJI.

257
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:19,666
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME, 
BRANDON, WE MISSED YOU.

258
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:21,733
YOU HAVEN'T FORGOTTEN
YOUR OLD PAL.

259
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:25,733
IT'S ME, BOB POUNDMAX,
REMEMBER?

260
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:30,033
OH, NO!  YOU'VE FORGOTTEN 
ALL ABOUT ME, HAVEN'T YOU?

261
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:32,800
YOU'RE NOT ONLY A TRAITOR,
YOU'RE A HEARTBREAKER TOO.

262
00:14:32,866 --> 00:14:35,400
HEY, BOSS, IF YOU DON'T MIND,

263
00:14:35,466 --> 00:14:37,266
I'D LIKE YOU TO
LEAVE THIS TO ME, ALL RIGHT?

264
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,933
- HE'S ALL YOURS.

265
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,500
- THANK YOU, BOSS.

266
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,200
- THIS IS THE CHANCE
YOU'VE BEEN WAITING FOR.

267
00:14:44,266 --> 00:14:47,533
MAKE SURE YOU SHOW THE TRAITOR
THAT NEW POWER OF YOURS.

268
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:50,800
- MAN, THIS IS GREAT. 
I GET TO USE MY POWERS

269
00:14:50,866 --> 00:14:52,566
AND GET RID OF A TRAITOR
AT THE SAME TIME.

270
00:14:52,633 --> 00:14:53,966
THANKS, LEE.

271
00:14:54,033 --> 00:14:56,766
- MAKE SURE THAT YOU 
 COOK HIM THOROUGHLY.

272
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:01,133
- ( grunts )

273
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,633
YO, BRANDON.

274
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:06,000
( groans )

275
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:13,000
IT HURTS, BRANDON.

276
00:15:13,066 --> 00:15:14,466
YOU'RE AN AWFUL
SNEAKY GUY,

277
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:17,533
PULLING A SURPRISE ATTACK
LIKE THAT ON AN OLD FRIEND.

278
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,233
IT MAKES ME SAD,

279
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:20,933
BRANDON!

280
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:23,933
- ( gasps )

281
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,900
- LOOKS LIKE A NASTY ONE.

282
00:15:27,966 --> 00:15:29,966
I TELL YOU,
THOSE FUNCTIONAL DISORDERS

283
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:31,200
CAN BE A REAL BITCH.

284
00:15:31,266 --> 00:15:32,566
THE SHAPE YOU'RE IN,

285
00:15:32,633 --> 00:15:34,933
YOU'RE NOT EVEN GONNA
BE ABLE TO KNOCK ME DOWN.

286
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,466
YOU KNOW WHY?

287
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:38,200
BECAUSE...

288
00:15:38,266 --> 00:15:42,133
BECAUSE I GOT
THIS <i>LITTLE</i> SURPRISE.

289
00:15:43,766 --> 00:15:46,666
POWER!  ENORMOUS POWER!

290
00:15:48,133 --> 00:15:50,433
A POWER BEYOND NECROLIZATION.

291
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:53,866
THIS IS THE POWER
OF A SUPERIOR!

292
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:58,000
- I SUPPOSE I'M JUST
FEELING NOSTALGIC,

293
00:15:58,066 --> 00:16:00,866
BUT I FIND MYSELF
PREOCCUPIED WITH THE PAST

294
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:02,900
AND WITH MY MEMORIES
OF THAT MAN.

295
00:16:02,966 --> 00:16:04,966
- HE BETRAYED
THE ORGANIZATION.

296
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:06,833
HE IS OUR ENEMY.

297
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,266
- YES, I KNOW.

298
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:09,933
IT'S JUST THAT
SEEING HIM AGAIN--

299
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,700
- IT'S NOT IMPORTANT.
FORGET IT.

300
00:16:11,766 --> 00:16:14,200
RIGHT NOW, BRANDON HEAT

301
00:16:14,266 --> 00:16:16,200
IS ABOUT TO GO BACK
TO HIS GRAVE AGAIN.

302
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:19,066
AND HE'S BEING SENT THERE
BY BOB POUNDMAX.

303
00:16:19,133 --> 00:16:20,600
- TRUE ENOUGH.

304
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,700
- BIG GUY.

305
00:16:28,766 --> 00:16:29,900
- ( explosion )

306
00:16:31,633 --> 00:16:33,266
( explosion )

307
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:35,066
- ( rumbling )

308
00:16:41,566 --> 00:16:43,066
- ( wind rushes )

309
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:45,633
- ( helicopter overhead )

310
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:48,400
- ( high-pitched laughter )

311
00:16:51,366 --> 00:16:54,100
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF A SUPERIOR'S POWER?

312
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:58,100
GO BACK TO YOUR
GRAVE AGAIN AND ROT!

313
00:16:58,166 --> 00:17:01,900
BRANDON!

314
00:17:11,133 --> 00:17:13,133
THAT'S NOT GONNA
WORK ON ME.

315
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:16,466
YOU CAN'T HURT A SUPERIOR
WITH THAT PEASHOOTER.

316
00:17:16,533 --> 00:17:18,500
TIME TO DIE, TRAITOR.

317
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:24,500
- ( gunshot )
- ( grunts ) 

318
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,500
- ( high-pitched laugh )

319
00:17:31,666 --> 00:17:33,400
( groans )
- ( grunts )

320
00:17:33,466 --> 00:17:35,766
- TOO MUCH FAT
 CAN KILL YOU.

321
00:17:37,766 --> 00:17:39,933
- ( grunting )

322
00:17:43,533 --> 00:17:46,500
( grunting )

323
00:17:49,566 --> 00:17:50,700
- WHAT'S THAT?

324
00:17:50,766 --> 00:17:52,466
- LET'S GO.

325
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,333
- ( wind rushes )

326
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:15,866
- THIS IS THE END.

327
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:20,366
( groaning )

328
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:24,700
HEY, BRANDON!

329
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:34,566
THIS IS THE POWER.

330
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:37,233
THIS IS THE POWER
THAT BALLADBIRD LEE GAVE ME.

331
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:39,066
THIS IS THE POWER...

332
00:18:39,133 --> 00:18:41,566
OF A SUPERIOR!

333
00:18:41,633 --> 00:18:46,433
( high-pitched laugh )

334
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,600
BRANDON!

335
00:18:53,166 --> 00:18:55,333
- ( whispers ) BRANDON.

336
00:18:55,400 --> 00:19:00,766
- Maria:
BRANDON, BRANDON.

337
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,133
- Brandon: MARIA.

338
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:05,766
- Young Harry:
BRANDON.  BRANDON.

339
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:08,800
- Brandon: HARRY.

340
00:19:08,866 --> 00:19:09,800
HARRY.

341
00:19:09,866 --> 00:19:12,566
- BRANDON.

342
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:13,733
BRANDON!

343
00:19:14,866 --> 00:19:16,466
BRANDON!

344
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:22,100
Mika: MY MOM WAS
MURDERED BY HARRY.

345
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:23,766
BY HARRY.

346
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,266
BY HARRY.

347
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,200
BY HARRY.

348
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,400
BY HARRY.

349
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,566
- Brandon: HARRY.

350
00:19:42,633 --> 00:19:45,333
- ( gunshots )

351
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,666
- ( screams )

352
00:19:50,133 --> 00:19:51,833
YOU BASTARD!

353
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:54,866
YOU THINK YOU'RE GONNA
GET OUT OF THIS ALIVE?

354
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:56,833
NOW YOU DIE, ASSHOLE!

355
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:58,766
( growling )

356
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,633
DON'T PRETEND
YOU'RE MR. COOL.

357
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,500
YOU'RE SCARED
OUT OF YOUR WITS.

358
00:20:02,566 --> 00:20:04,300
( growls )

359
00:20:10,633 --> 00:20:12,033
( groans )

360
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:16,633
YOU'LL PAY FOR THIS!

361
00:20:26,033 --> 00:20:27,933
( groans )

362
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:33,033
REPLICATION SYSTEMS
OVERLOADING!

363
00:20:39,533 --> 00:20:41,333
( gasps )

364
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,533
I'M A SUPERIOR.
( gasps )

365
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:46,733
I WAS SUPPOSED TO HAVE
GOTTEN STRONGER.

366
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:50,166
I WAS SUPPOSED TO
HAVE BECOME UNBEATABLE.

367
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,500
( gasps )
- ( footsteps approaching )

368
00:20:52,566 --> 00:20:54,466
- BRANDON, I--

369
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:56,400
- BOB.

370
00:20:56,466 --> 00:20:59,333
BOB POUNDMAX.

371
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:02,566
- BRANDON, DO--
YOU KNOW ME.

372
00:21:02,633 --> 00:21:04,000
YOU KNOW WHO I AM.

373
00:21:04,066 --> 00:21:05,633
YOU REMEMBER ME, RIGHT?

374
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:08,266
PLEASE HELP ME, BRANDON.
I'M BEGGING YOU.

375
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:10,000
WE JOINED THE FAMILY
TOGETHER.

376
00:21:10,066 --> 00:21:12,466
WE WERE PALS.
REMEMBER?

377
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:15,333
BRANDON, REMEMBER THAT
TWO MILLION YULE

378
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,033
I BORROWED 19 YEARS AGO?

379
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:19,166
WELL, NOW I CAN PAY YOU BACK
WITH INTEREST.

380
00:21:19,233 --> 00:21:21,766
WILL YOU HELP ME, BRANDON?

381
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:23,166
PLEASE.

382
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:25,933
LEE, YOU GOTTA SAVE ME!

383
00:21:30,233 --> 00:21:32,566
HEY, BRANDON?

384
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:33,700
( grunts )

385
00:21:33,766 --> 00:21:36,100
( groans )

386
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:39,200
( grunts, wheezes )

387
00:21:39,266 --> 00:21:42,533
BRANDON!

388
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:51,100
( screaming )
- ( gunfire )

389
00:21:51,166 --> 00:21:52,733
( gunfire ceases )

390
00:22:04,666 --> 00:22:07,066
- Mika: GRAVE.  GRAVE!

391
00:22:11,366 --> 00:22:13,266
HI, GRAVE.

392
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:14,900
I'M GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

393
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:16,866
WHAT'S WRONG?

394
00:22:16,933 --> 00:22:18,366
YOU AREN'T HURT, ARE YOU?

395
00:22:18,433 --> 00:22:20,733
WHAT IS IT?

396
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:33,400
- Grave: TO PROTECT--

397
00:22:33,466 --> 00:22:35,466
TO PROTECT THIS GIRL,

398
00:22:35,533 --> 00:22:37,533
THAT IS WHAT
MILLENNION IS TO ME.

399
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:40,000
IT'S MY WAY OF LIFE.

400
00:22:44,966 --> 00:22:48,333
- ( theme music playing )

401
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:59,733
- ( singing in Japanese )

402
00:24:15,166 --> 00:24:16,766
- Grave: BIG GUY--

403
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:19,733
A NOSTALGIC NICKNAME
EVOKING PAST INNOCENCE,

404
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,866
BUT IT'S
AN INVITATION TO WAR.

405
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:25,066
A MAN CAN'T GO BACK

406
00:24:25,133 --> 00:24:27,933
EVEN FOR THE SAKE
OF HIS OWN BELIEFS.

